name: Titanium.UI.iOS.3DMatrix
doc:
@platform iphone 0.9 @platform ipad 0.9 @editurl https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/edit/master/apidoc/Titanium/UI/iOS/3DMatrix.yml

The 3D Matrix is an object for holding values for a 3D affine transform.

deprecated.text:
2.1.0 Use instead. @description

The 3DMatrix is created by {@link Titanium.UI.iOS#method-create3DMatrix}. A 3D transform is used to rotate, scale, translate, or skew the objects in three-dimensional space. A 3D transform is represented by a 4 by 4 matrix.

You create an identity matrix by creating a 3D Matrix with an empty constructor.

See {@link Titanium.UI.3DMatrix} for sample usage.

property.name: apiName
property.doc:
The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.

@description

The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, Button returns Ti.UI.Button.

@platform android 3.2.0 @platform blackberry 3.2.0 @platform iphone 3.2.0 @platform ipad 3.2.0 @platform mobileweb 3.2.0
property.shortDoc: The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to. ...

property.name: bubbleParent
property.doc:
Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent.

@description

Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often established by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a click event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are table sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views to their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.

@platform android 3.0.0 @platform iphone 3.0.0 @platform ipad 3.0.0
property.shortDoc: Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent. ...

property.name: lifecycleContainer
property.doc:
The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.

@description

If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks will also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set to the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.

@platform android 3.6.0
property.shortDoc: The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy. ...

method.name: multiply
method.doc: Returns a matrix constructed by combining two existing matrices.

params.name: t2
params.doc:
The second matrix. This matrix is concatenated to the matrix instance against which the function is invoked. The result of this function is the first matrix multiplied by the second matrix. You might perform several multiplications in order to create a single matrix that contains the cumulative effects of several transformations.

Note that matrix operations are not commutative - the order in which you concatenate matrices is important. That is, the result of multiplying matrix t1 by matrix t2 does not necessarily equal the result of multiplying matrix t2 by matrix t1.

method.shortDoc: Returns a matrix constructed by combining two existing matrices. ...

method.name: removeEventListener
method.doc:
Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.

@description

Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the callback parameter is used to determine which listener to remove.

When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function in order to remove the listener later:

var listener = function() { Ti.API.info("Event listener called."); }
window.addEventListener('click', listener);

To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:

window.removeEventListener('click', listener);

params.name: callback
params.doc: Callback function to remove. Must be the same function passed to addEventListener.

method.shortDoc: Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...

method.doc: Returns a matrix constructed by rotating an existing matrix.

params.name: angle
params.doc: The angle, in degrees, by which to rotate the matrix. A positive value specifies counterclockwise rotation and a negative value specifies clockwise rotation.

params.name: x
params.doc: The x coordinate of the vector about which to rotate.

params.name: y
params.doc: The y coordinate of the vector about which to rotate.

params.name: z
params.doc: The z coordinate of the vector about which to rotate.

method.shortDoc: Returns a matrix constructed by rotating an existing matrix. ...

method.name: translate
method.doc: Returns a matrix constructed by translating an existing matrix.

params.name: tx
params.doc: The value by which to move x values with the matrix.

params.name: ty
params.doc: The value by which to move y values with the matrix. Negative values move the target up the display whereas towards the user and negative values away from the user.

params.name: tz
params.doc: The value by which to move z values with the matrix. Negative values move the target towards the user whereas negative values away from the user.
